#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:5
msgid "AD4062 driver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:7
msgid ""
"ADC driver for Analog Devices Inc. AD4060/AD4062 devices. The module name is "
"``ad4062``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:11
msgid "Supported devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:13
msgid "The following chips are supported by this driver:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:15
msgid "`AD4060 <https://www.analog.com/AD4060>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:16
msgid "`AD4062 <https://www.analog.com/AD4062>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:19
msgid "Wiring modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:21
msgid ""
"The ADC is interfaced through an I3C bus, and contains two programmable "
"GPIOs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:23
msgid ""
"The ADC convert-start happens on the SDA rising edge of the I3C stop (P) bit "
"at the end of the read command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:26
msgid ""
"The two programmable GPIOS are optional and have a role assigned if present "
"in the devicetree ``interrupt-names`` property:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:29
msgid "GP0: Is assigned the role of Threshold Either signal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:30
msgid "GP1: Is assigned the role of Data Ready signal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:32
msgid ""
"If the property ``gpio-controller`` is present in the devicetree, then the "
"GPO not present in the ``interrupt-names`` is exposed as a GPO."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:36 ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:61
msgid "Device attributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:38
msgid "The ADC contains only one channel with following attributes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:40
msgid "Channel attributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:43 ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:64
#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:123
msgid "Attribute"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:44 ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:65
#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:124
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:45
msgid "``in_voltage_calibscale``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:46
msgid ""
"Sets the gain scaling factor that the hardware applies to the sample, to "
"compensate for system gain error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:48
msgid "``in_voltage_oversampling_ratio``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:49
msgid ""
"Sets device's burst averaging mode to over sample using the internal sample "
"rate. Value 1 disable the burst averaging mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:51
msgid "``in_voltage_oversampling_ratio_available``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:52
msgid "List of available oversampling values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:53
msgid "``in_voltage_raw``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:54
msgid "Returns the raw ADC voltage value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:55
msgid "``in_voltage_scale``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:56
msgid ""
"Returns the channel scale in reference to the reference voltage ``ref-"
"supply`` or ``vdd-supply`` if the former not present."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:59
msgid "Also contain the following device attributes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:66 ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:125
msgid "``sampling_frequency``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:67
msgid ""
"Sets the duration of a single scan, used in the burst averaging mode. The "
"duration is described by ``(n_avg - 1) / fosc + tconv``, where ``n_avg`` is "
"the oversampling ratio, ``fosc`` is the internal sample rate and ``tconv`` "
"is the ADC conversion time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:71 ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:128
msgid "``sampling_frequency_available``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:72
msgid ""
"Lists the available sampling frequencies, computed on the current "
"oversampling ratio. If the ratio is 1, the frequency is ``1/tconv``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:76
msgid "Interrupts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:78
msgid ""
"The interrupts are mapped through the ``interrupt-names`` and ``interrupts`` "
"properties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:81
msgid ""
"The ``interrupt-names`` ``gp0`` entry sets the role of Threshold signal, and "
"entry ``gp1`` the role of Data Ready signal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:84
msgid ""
"If each is not present, the driver fallback to enabling the same role as an "
"I3C IBI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:88
msgid "Low-power mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:90
msgid ""
"The device enters low-power mode on idle to save power. Enabling an event "
"puts the device out of the low-power since the ADC autonomously samples to "
"assert the event condition."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:95
msgid "IIO trigger support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:97
msgid ""
"An IIO trigger ``ad4062-devX`` is registered by the driver to be used by the "
"same device, to capture samples to a software buffer. It is required to "
"attach the trigger to the device by setting the ``current_trigger`` before "
"enabling and reading the buffer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:102
msgid ""
"The acquisition is sequential and bounded by the protocol timings, software "
"latency and internal timings, the sample rate is not configurable. The burst "
"averaging mode does impact the effective sample rate, since it increases the "
"internal timing to output a single sample."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:108
msgid "Threshold events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:110
msgid ""
"The ADC supports a monitoring mode to raise threshold events. The driver "
"supports a single interrupt for both rising and falling readings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:113
msgid ""
"The feature is enabled/disabled by setting ``thresh_either_en``. During "
"monitor mode, the device continuously operates in autonomous mode. Any "
"register access puts the device back in configuration mode, due to this, any "
"access disables monitor mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:118
msgid "The following event attributes are available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:120
msgid "Event attributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:126
msgid ""
"Frequency used in the monitoring mode, sets the device internal sample rate "
"when the mode is activated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:129
msgid "List of available sample rates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:130
msgid "``thresh_either_en``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:131
msgid "Enable monitoring mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:132
msgid "``thresh_falling_hysteresis``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:133
msgid "Set the hysteresis value for the minimum threshold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:134
msgid "``thresh_falling_value``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:135
msgid "Set the minimum threshold value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:136
msgid "``thresh_rising_hysteresis``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:137
msgid "Set the hysteresis value for the maximum threshold."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:138
msgid "``thresh_rising_value``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:139
msgid "Set the maximum threshold value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:142
msgid "GPO controller support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../iio/ad4062.rst:144
msgid ""
"The device supports using GP0 and GP1 as GPOs. If the devicetree contains "
"the node ``gpio-controller```, the device is marked as a GPIO controller and "
"the GPs not listed in ``interrupt-names`` are exposed as a GPO. The GPIO "
"index matches the pin name, so if GP0 is not exposed but GP1 is, index 0 is "
"masked out and only index 1 can be set."
msgstr ""
